{{BLP sources|date=November 2014}} '''Allan Casey''' is a [[Canadian]] writer, whose book ''[[Lakeland: Journeys into the Soul of Canada]]'', won the [[2010 Governor General's Awards|Governor General's Award]] for [[Governor General's Award for English language non-fiction|English non-fiction]] in 2010.<ref>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/arts/books/reginas-dianne-warren-wins-gov-gen-award-for-cool-water/article1800968/ "Regina's Dianne Warren wins Gov-Gen Award for ‘Cool Water’"]. ''The Globe and Mail'', November 16, 2010.</ref> The book was also a shortlisted nominee for the [[Edna Staebler Award]].<ref>[http://www.wlu.ca/news_detail.php?grp_id=0&nws_id=6813 "News Release: Shortlist announced for 2010 Edna Staebler Award for Creative Non-Fiction"]. Wilfrid Laurier University, September 13, 2010.</ref>
Born in [[Regina, Saskatchewan]], and raised in [[Prince Albert, Saskatchewan|Prince Albert]], Casey has written for a variety of publications, including ''[[Adbusters]]'', ''[[Canadian Business]]'', ''[[Canadian Geographic]]'',<ref>[http://www.canadiangeographic.ca/magazine/back_issues/contributor.asp?contrib=Allan_Casey&id=1076 Articles by Allan Casey at ''Canadian Geographic''].</ref> ''[[Canadian Living]]'', ''[[Reader's Digest]]'' and ''[[Books in Canada]]''.
