'''Green Key Global''' is an international [[eco-label]] which certifies hotels and venues operating in 20 countries. The industry-run group is based in [[Ottawa]] and has over 1,800 participating facilities.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mic.com/articles/182560/any-hotel-can-call-itself-green-we-investigated-exactly-what-that-means#.t4v1Z6LOk|title=Any hotel can call itself "green" — we investigated exactly what that means|last=Firshein|first=Sarah|date=21 July 2017|work=[[Mic (media company)|Mic]]|access-date=28 July 2018}}</ref> The system is based on self-reporting, with facilities receiving a certification between one and five keys.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.meetingscanada.com/fairmont-joins-green-key-eco-rating-program-in-us/|title=Fairmont Joins Green Key Eco-Rating Program in U.S.|last=Douloff|first=Don|date=23 September 2009|work=Meetings Canada|access-date=28 July 2018}}</ref>

